# Nocturne Windows 11 Widget

The Nocturne widget puts your live glucose on the Windows 11 Widgets Board — the
panel that opens with **Win + W**. It reads from any Nocturne server you have access
to (hosted or self-hosted) and refreshes on its own.

It comes in three sizes:

| Size | Name in the picker | Shows |
|------|--------------------|-------|
| Small | Nocturne (Small) | Glucose value and trend arrow |
| Medium | Nocturne | Glucose, trend, delta, insulin-on-board and carbs-on-board |
| Large | Nocturne Dashboard | Everything in Medium, plus short-term predictions and tracker ages |

You can add more than one — for example a Small widget for a quick number and a
Large one for the full picture.

## Requirements

- Windows 11 (build 22000 or later)
- A Nocturne account on a server you can sign in to

## Install

The widget installs from the **Microsoft Store** — search for "Nocturne" in the
Store app, or on the Widgets Board itself. Store installs are signed by Microsoft,
update automatically, and need no extra setup.

<Callout type="info" title="Before the Store listing is live">
  While the Store listing is being prepared, you can build and sideload the widget
  from source. See the
  <a href="https://github.com/nightscout/nocturne/tree/main/src/Widgets/Nocturne.Widget.Windows11">widget README</a>
  for the developer install steps.
</Callout>

## Add the widget to your board

1. Press **Win + W** to open the Widgets Board.
2. Click the **+** (Add widgets) button.
3. Search for **Nocturne** and choose the size you want.

The widget appears showing **Setup Required** until you connect it to your server.

## Connect to your Nocturne server

The widget signs in with a short code — there are no tokens or passwords to copy.

1. Right-click the widget and choose **Customize**.
2. Enter your **Nocturne server URL** (for example `https://your-nocturne-server.com`) and click **Connect**.
3. The widget shows a short code and a link. Click **Open in Browser**, sign in to
   Nocturne if needed, and approve the request.
4. Once approved, the widget switches to showing your glucose automatically.

The widget asks only for **read-only** access — glucose, treatments (for IOB/COB),
device status, and therapy settings used for display. It can never change anything
on your server.

<Callout type="tip" title="Connecting more than one widget">
  You only need to do this once. After the first widget is connected, additional
  Nocturne widgets on the same PC use the same connection.
</Callout>

## What each size shows

- **Small** — the current glucose value and trend arrow.
- **Medium** — adds the delta since the previous reading, insulin-on-board (IOB),
  and carbs-on-board (COB).
- **Large** — adds predicted values at +15 / +30 / +45 / +60 minutes (when your
  server provides predictions) and the ages of your active trackers (such as site
  or sensor), highlighted when one needs attention.

When a reading is older than expected, the widget marks it as stale so you can tell
the number isn't current.

## Refreshing

The widget updates on its own and whenever you reopen the Widgets Board. To force an
immediate update, use the **Refresh** action on the widget.

## Disconnecting

To disconnect a PC from your server:

- Open the widget's **Customize** panel and choose **Sign out**. This revokes the
  connection and removes the stored tokens from that PC; or
- From your Nocturne account, open the connected-apps settings and revoke
  **Nocturne Windows Widget**.

Either method takes effect immediately.

## Troubleshooting

**The widget isn't in the Add widgets list.**
Close and reopen the Widgets Board (Win + W). If it still doesn't appear right after
installing, sign out of Windows and back in so the board re-scans for new widgets.

**It still says "Setup Required".**
You haven't connected it yet — follow [Connect to your Nocturne server](#connect-to-your-nocturne-server).

**It shows a connection error or no data.**
Check that the server URL is correct and reachable from this PC in a browser. If the
URL is right but it still fails, open **Customize**, **Sign out**, and connect again.

**The number looks out of date.**
The widget shows whatever your server has. If the reading is stale, the issue is
upstream (your CGM uploader or data source), not the widget.

## Privacy

The widget talks only to the server you configure. Your data and sign-in tokens stay
on your PC and that server; nothing is sent to the Nightscout Foundation and there is
no tracking. Full details are in the
[widget privacy policy](/docs/windows-widget-privacy).
